    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-07-29T04:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-07-29T04:00:00-05:00" n="960"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d960">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">123 Stuart, J. Leighton: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stuart</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Nanking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-07-29T17:00:00+08:00"
                            >July 29, 1949—5 p. m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received July 29—5:26 a. m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1644. Please inform appropriate authorities CAF that I intend depart Nanking for
                    Okinawa in Embassy plane Monday August 1, 8 a.m. (see Embtel 1532, July 15 to
                    Department, repeated Canton 642, Taipei 63). Information contained in reftel
                    still holds.</p>
                <p>Sent OffEmb Canton 692, Taipei 70, repeated Department.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stuart</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
